reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Durable , easy to assemble , nice looking
reviews.reviewText: My dishwasher Stopped working and hubby has been too busy to install the new one.I’m back to washing by hand.with a family of 6 Washing dishes has become a full time job! I needed something space saving and durable. This had worked out perfectly!I love my new dish rack. I forgot how relaxing washing dishes can be and this new addition to my kitchen adds to it.It was easy to assemble. The instructions were very clear and easy to follow. I actually had my 11 and 15-year-old boys put it together for me..It's not at all heavy, but it's sturdy.Very well constructed..well-proportioned, maximizes the space that it takes. I love the over the sink design- when I open the window, It helps to dry the dishes faster.the excess water conveniently drips right Down into the sink and no more nasty, slimy, moldy, rubber mat underneath your clean dishes that you find with traditional countertop styles.Overall awesome space saving solution, versatile and a place for everything!!Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Kitchen Counter Marvel
reviews.reviewText: Pros:1. **Space-Saving Design:** The over-the-sink configuration optimizes kitchen space efficiently, making the MOUKABAL dish drying rack a great solution for smaller kitchens or those seeking to maximize counter space.2. **Two-Tier Utensil Holder:** The inclusion of a two-tier utensil holder adds an extra layer of organization, allowing for the efficient drying of various kitchen tools and utensils, enhancing overall kitchen functionality.3. **Large Stainless Steel Build:** The robust stainless steel construction not only ensures durability but also adds a sleek and modern aesthetic to the kitchen. The material is resistant to rust and corrosion, contributing to the rack's long-lasting performance.Cons:1. **Size Limitation:** While suitable for sinks up to 33 inches, the MOUKABAL dish drying rack may not be the ideal choice for larger sinks. Users with oversized sinks may need to measure carefully to ensure a proper fit.2. **Assembly Required:** Some users may find the assembly process a bit time-consuming or complex, and clear instructions would be beneficial to streamline the setup process.3. **Limited Color Options:** The availability of the dish drying rack in a single color may be limiting for those who prefer more variety to match their kitchen decor.4. **Price Consideration:** The premium stainless steel build may come with a slightly higher price point compared to other dish drying rack options. However, the added durability and aesthetic appeal justify the investment.Final Statement:The MOUKABAL Over-The-Sink Dish Drying Rack proves to be a valuable addition to any kitchen, especially for those with limited counter space. Its space-saving design, two-tier utensil holder, durable stainless steel build, and modern aesthetic make it a practical and visually appealing choice. Despite some considerations like size limitations and assembly requirements, the overall functionality and quality make it a recommended investment for an organized and efficient kitchen setup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I love it.
reviews.reviewText: Very easy to assemble. Pretty sturdy, but, it's not a solid piece and you need to remember that. I love that u can move the hooks, I put all, but 2, on front rail, since, back sits over back edge of my sink where faucet n handles are--in an old trailer and not that big of a sink or counter or kitchen. And you can change where the racks the dishes go on easily, since, they just hook over rails. They are 3 different designs. Only thing I didn't like is -the side rack for silverware and knives is over the counter and I don't have room to put the cutting board holder on outside of frame on the other side. So-I put it on inside and put my old silverware holder on it-lol. Gotta get a different one tho. Mines square and need an oblong 1. I was pleasantly surprised how easy it was to put together and move and I like the design. I bought it for the 2 layers so I could get some things off counter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars I like it. It does the job.
reviews.reviewText: It’s ok. It does the job. Easy to put together took about 30mins. Because the rack goes over the sink I have so much more counter space in my kitchen. I just dont like how it covers up my kitchen window. They could have made the 2nd shelf a little lower cause it’s not tall enough for my plates. My plates are too big. It’s kind of hard to get my plates in and out. Also the rack that holds the soap isn’t big enough for a big bottle of dish soap so I just put my sponges in it.
Esta compra fue excelente, todo cabe perfecto, no se oxidan y es súper resistente

Tiene bastante espacio, es muy funcional si lo que quieres es evitar que te estorben los platos, su altura está bien, yo le tuve que poner un poco de madera abajo de las patas, pues chocaba con mi grifo, pero no es nada que no se pueda solucionar.Se me hizo un excelente escurridor, los materiales no se ven tan resistentes, pero por ahora si que han tenido resistencia y durabilidad. A mi me encantó.

I have been looking at these for about a year, trying to decide if it was worth the money. FYI -- it is! I love that I now have extra counter space. This was super easy to put together. Took about 10 minutes. Everything needed to assemble was included. It holds alot of dishes. (We are a family of four). We put the hooks on the front and use them for hanging the cutting board and such for drying. I was worried about the sturdiness because this one cost way less than some of the others I saw, but no need to worry at all. This is definitely worth the money! I am super happy I finally bought it.
Me encanto y cumple su función a la perfección.

Espero que sí sea de acero inoxidable como lo indica, porque vivo en un lugar muy húmedo y casi cada 3 meses tengo que cambiar de escurrido porque se oxidan.Se veía algo frágil, pero al momento de armarlo se sintió más resistente.
